# E2E: `enozunu summon` materializes a selected source into its Claude-native path.
#
# Uses a `local` provider source so the happy path stays deterministic and
# offline: a git source would depend on an external repository and the network.

case "summon materializes a local skill source" {
  write <"sources/demo-skill/SKILL.md"> ```
    ---
    name: demo-skill
    description: demo skill for the summon happy path
    ---

    # Demo Skill
    ```
  write <"enozunu.kdl"> ```
    enozunu config-version=1 {
      provider {
        skills {
          skill "demo-skill" {
            local {
              path "sources/demo-skill"
            }
          }
        }
      }
      consumer {
        claude {
          use-skills "demo-skill"
        }
      }
    }
    ```
  $ enozunu summon
  assert {
    exit 0
    stdout contains "materialized"
    file <".claude/skills/demo-skill/SKILL.md"> contains "demo skill for the summon happy path"
    file <".enozunu/provenance.json"> contains "demo-skill"
  }
}
